# Documentation: commit and push

When you change documentation in this repo (root `*.md`, `README*`, `CHANGELOG`, `how-to-use*`, `STORE_PUBLISH*`, `private-policy*`, and `*.md` under `deploy/` or `docs/`), finish by **committing and pushing to `origin`** on the current branch unless the user explicitly says not to commit or push.

- Stage only doc-related files (not `dist/`, `node_modules/`, or unrelated code).
- Use a clear `docs:` commit message describing the doc change.
- Do not change git config; no force push or destructive git commands.
